                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Amazon.com:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1">Dave Hemsath and Leslie Yerkes have long believed that work need not be  bland and boring, and that a fun workplace is truly more productive than a dull one. To  check their theory, they asked successful businesspeople worldwide if fun played a  part in their corporate culture--and, if so, how it was actually manifested in everyday  life. <i>301 Ways to Have Fun at Work</i> is their lighthearted compendium of the  most useful and creative replies.</span>
              
</td></tr></table>
